To import an sql file to a mysql database for a shared hosting you can follow the steps given below

1. Access the DB Manager from the url http://serverpointapps.com
2. Enter the database username and password to login to the DB Manager.
3. Select database you need to restore from the drop down menu on the left side of the screen then click on "USE" button
1. Click on black screen icon on top-left corner of the screen and a new screen will be appear.
1. There you can execute the sql query or there is a "File upload" option which can be used to import the sql file from your local machine.
1.  Click on Choose File button and browse the sql file
1. Click on "Execute" Option and it will import the tables to the database
